  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The forthcoming book, \"Zootechnologies,\" published by Routledge in 2025, presents a novel exploration of the intersection between technology and animal husbandry. While specific metrics of engagement are currently unrecorded, the work's potential relevance to sustainability and policy is underscored by its inferred connection to Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Zootechnologies\" promises to be an important addition to the literature on animal husbandry and technological applications in farming. Scheduled for publication in 2025 by Routledge, this work aims to bridge the gap between traditional agriculture and modern technological advances, addressing critical issues surrounding sustainability and efficiency in livestock management.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred strength of the book's relevance to sustainability and policy is indicated by a moderately high association score of 0.55, suggesting that themes explored within may resonate with ongoing discussions in the field. This level of engagement underscores the potential for \"Zootechnologies\" to contribute meaningfully to dialogues about sustainable agricultural practices and regulatory frameworks that govern them.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the book shows a significant commercial engagement potential, being linked to platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. Such connection suggests an opportunity for the text to reach a wider audience, extending beyond academia into commercial and public spheres. Despite the lack of formal citations and online mentions at this time, the commercial linkage signals a readiness for broader societal discourse.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While specific metrics detailing community engagement are absent, the work's focus on the evolving role of technology in animal agriculture suggests a future capacity to generate considerable discussion. As society increasingly grapples with food security and environmental sustainability, \"Zootechnologies\" is positioned to be a relevant resource addressing these pressing issues, allowing it to serve as a foundation for future research and conversation in both academic and policymaking arenas.</p>",
